Name: Spawn of Arcadia
Description:
A glassy jellyfish, lights pulsing beneath its skin. Its thin tentacles pluck at the air, their vibrations manipulating the space around its body.

As it writhes, a faint music drifts from its tendrils, worming its way into your ears. The melody seems to never end, worming its way into your ears, never ending, worming its way into your ears, never ending, never...

Name: Soil De-wormer
Description: A control unit for a brigade of tiny robots. These are directed to burrow through the soil and eliminate yield-depleting pests. Control unit maintenance is crucial to prevent accidental robot swarms.

Name: Auto Sprinkler
Description: An automatic sprinkler system that tunes itself to the needs of the plants, deploying water as a fine mist, a heavy downpour, or anything in-between.

Name: Light Balancer
Description: A bank of LEDs controlled by a photosensitive processing unit, designed to carefully deliver exactly the mix of red, green or blue light that the plant requires.

Name: Auto-propagator
Description: This advanced bank of lasers prunes and propagates plants as required, the cauterising light offering unequaled precision.

Name: Nutrient Distributor
Description: A hybrid fabricator/distributor that tests the soil for missing nutrients, so that it can create and spray the perfect fertiliser.

Name: Fuel Inverter
Description: A piece of rechargeable power technology. The fuel inverter ensures an even flow of power to autonomous machines.

Name: Membrane Battery
Description: The membrane battery is an almost maintenance-free piece of rechargeable power technology. Nestled among in the machine's circuits, it supplies power safely and directly.

Name: Power Condenser
Description: A piece of rechargeable power technology. The power condenser harvests any heat energy wasted during the machine's operation, and uses it to generate extra power.

Name: Generator Coupling
Description: The generator coupling is an important piece of the machine's rechargeable power systems. Without it, the generator would fruitlessly spin, pumping power out into the void.

Name: Kinetic Dynamo
Description: The kinetic dynamo takes a small initial charge and uses it to run power-harvesting systems that tap into the orbit of the planet. This frees autonomous machinery from frequent fuel inspections, allowing them to endure extremely long maintenance cycles.

Name: Furnace Tank
Description:
High-temperature burn unit, designed to consume a wide range of biological material. Insert materials to initiate burn.

When active, drives an internal turbine to generate power.

As it writhes, a faint music drifts from its tendrils, worming its way into your ears. The melody seems to never end, worming its way into your ears, never ending, worming its way into your ears, never ending, never...

Name: Homeworld Repeater
Description:
A makeshift device, cobbled from salvaged electronic components kept in deep storage for many years. This jumble of wires will attempt to make contact with the last-known remnants of the freighter's homeworld.

Select the device and select Broadcast (FE_ALT1) to begin the location process.

Name: Debris Rangefinder
Description:
A single-use device for locating the wreckage of starships in deep space.

Select the Rangefinder and Scan for Debris (FE_ALT1) to begin the location process.
